A vintage 1960s-style illustration of a command center desk viewed from above, featuring an elegant wooden desktop with organized compartments displaying miniature representations of daily work life: tiny envelope stacks sorted by urgency, a circular rotating card file with portrait silhouettes of colleagues, a small calendar wheel showing meeting blocks, and brass gauges with needle indicators showing counts and metrics. The scene is bathed in warm amber desk lamp light, with rich mahogany browns, cream papers, and touches of brass and hunter green. The aesthetic evokes mid-century modern design with clean lines and purposeful organization, suggesting productivity and control over one's workday without any digital screens visible.
